The word "best-selling" can refer to items with the highest sales figures or quantities. In this context, "best-selling" is determined by a combination of both total sales amount and total quantity sold, with the highest sales taking precedence over quantity.;
"Products" in the query refer to items in retail or inventory management. They are identified uniquely by `item_id` and have a name (`item_identifier`).;
"Outlets" are retail stores or sales points, each with a unique `outlet_id` and an identifier (`outlet_identifier`).;
The maximum retail price (`item_mrp`) is the suggested or maximum price at which an item is supposed to be sold, reflecting its market value.;

sql:
SELECT year, AVG(CASE WHEN outlet_status = 'operational' THEN 365 ELSE 0 END) AS avg_days_operational
FROM outlet_years
GROUP BY year;
